race.comment: PINK LAMBORGHINI (6) switched from a Victorian yard and led and won her Maiden here first-up heavily bet. Tackled stronger than this at Gundagai following, beaten just 1.7L. Presents fitter again with Newitt a key jockey booking. She can bounce. FORCEFILLY (2) was quickly back in the winner's circle, winning this grade at Nowra. Maps for the run of the race and benefits from a handy 3kg claim. In good hands and should go close. COOL AS POPEYE (10) was quickly on track winning her Maiden at Goulburn. Overcame a slipped saddle and expect the form to stack up. TILLMAN (5) threatened here three times before being outgraded at Canberra 5 days ago. Must be pleasing and is in well with the 3kg claim. Consider.
